The '''"2am Lockout"''', or simply '''"The Lockout"''', is the name of an initiative set up by the [[Government of Victoria (Australia)|Victorian Government]] to curb alcohol-related violence in [[Melbourne, Victoria|Melbourne]]. Currently in a three month trial period that begun on [[June 2]], [[2008]], the lockout prohibits patrons from entering pubs, bars and nightclubs after 2am in designated areas which include the council areas of [[City of Port Phillip|Port Phillip]], [[City of Stonnington|Stonnington]], [[City of Melbourne|Melbourne]] and [[City of Yarra|Yarra]]. Licensees who breach the lockout are  can be fined a maximum of $6899.

==Controversy==
*On the first morning of the trial at 04:30, a bouncer strikes a reveller outside a bar. John Brumby uses the incident to justify the lockout.<ref>{{cite news | first= | last= | coauthors= | title=Bouncer's attack 'justifies 2am lockout' | date=[[2008-06-02]] | publisher=News.com.au | url =http://www.news.com.au/story/0,23599,23795450-2,00.html?from=public_rss | work =Herald Sun | pages = | accessdate = 2008-06-03 | language = }}</ref>

